comments.body: @axamei  Looks like it is still open under captcha? (was going to close an old SN@P ticket and checked)
@kevinreiss try it in new/private browser. i get the following:
I'm available to discuss details of the current AbID database and the functions it supports for MARC records.  Also, there's a little more to it than simply generating new AbIDs.
@doncat If the "more" is not reflected in the above, could you elaborate?

Barcodes generated without AbID, for ReCAP "EAD" type.  AbID replacement is only for onsite storage.
Also, those search options on the Start form were created per user request.  It has been useful (on rare occasions, I think) to see what was assigned to an item in case of mistaken changes in EAD or MARC.
Also note the "None" metadata option for odd cases, mostly Cotsen boxes.
@axamei could we check to see if the bug has been fixed since we first noticed this.
